# Consistent Iconography

Do NOT invent or swap in new icons/glyphs for a concept that already has an
established glyph in this codebase. Reuse what exists so the whole system stays
cohesive. When adding a new UI element, first grep for an existing example of the
same concept and match its glyph exactly.

## Deltas / trend indicators

Trend + status deltas use plain **arrows**, not triangles:

- Up  → `↑` (`&#8593;` in HTML, `\u2191` in JS) — never `▲` / `&#9650;` / `\u25b2`
- Down → `↓` (`&#8595;` in HTML, `\u2193` in JS) — never `▼` / `&#9660;` / `\u25bc`

Applies to `.pg-delta` (playground) and `.p2p-kdelta` / `.p2p-delta` (P2P views).

```html
<!-- BAD -->  <span class="pg-delta up">&#9650; 8%</span>
<!-- GOOD --> <span class="pg-delta up">&#8593; 8%</span>
```

## Delta styling

KPI-card deltas render as a tinted rounded **pill** (`padding:3px 8px;
border-radius:999px;` + a `color-mix` background), matching `.pg-delta`. Keep the
P2P polarity: `.up` = danger (red), `.down` = success (green).
